---
import ProjectLayout from "../../components/ProjectLayout.astro";
import TechIcon from "../../components/TechIcon.astro";
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="RWE Energy — Platform Migration"
  description="Case study: migrating a legacy Java monolith to Node.js microservices for Germany's largest energy company"
>
  <main>
    <section
      class="project-hero"
      style="background: var(--dark); color: white; padding: 5rem 0 3.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; text-align: center; position: relative;"
    >
      <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">
        <h1
          style="font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          RWE Energy Platform
        </h1>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.35rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; line-height: 1.6;"
        >
          Migrating a slow Java monolith to a modern Node.js stack for one of
          Germany's largest energy companies
        </p>
        <div
          style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;"
        >
          <span
            style="padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 50px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.85rem; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);"
          >
            ENTERPRISE
          </span>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/calindotgabriel/energy-reporter"
            style="padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem; background: white; color: var(--dark); border-radius: 50px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.85rem; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease;"
          >
            View on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <article style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px;">

      <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          The Problem
        </h2>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        >
          RWE's energy services platform was running on a legacy Java monolith that was
          slow and poorly implemented. Energy market data needed to be queried, filtered,
          and exported daily — but the system couldn't keep up. Large dataset exports
          took 45 minutes. API responses were sluggish. The monolith was hard to maintain
          and even harder to extend.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray);"
        >
          The business needed a system that could handle thousands of daily energy market
          queries with fast, reliable responses — and a codebase that a small team could
          actually evolve without fear.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- THE APPROACH -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          How I Approached It
        </h2>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        >
          We migrated to Node.js with NestJS and MongoDB — a stack that gave us the
          modularity and performance the monolith lacked. Energy projects have dynamic
          properties, so the filtering system needed to generate columns on the fly based
          on each project's characteristics. I built this with MongoDB aggregations
          optimized through profiling, not guesswork.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        >
          The biggest technical challenge was that heavy data processing was killing the
          main thread. I implemented <strong>Worker Pools</strong> to offload large dataset
          operations to parallel threads — this is what brought export times from 45 minutes
          down to 12. I used the Node.js profiler to find the actual bottlenecks rather than
          optimizing blind.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray);"
        >
          One thing I did without being asked: I introduced <strong>TDD from the start</strong>
          for every feature I built. On a migration project — where you're replacing a running
          system people depend on — you need the confidence that tests give you. I made that
          call early, and it paid off immediately. This discipline later became second nature
          when I moved to Scout24, where full test coverage was already the norm.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- WHAT I DELIVERED -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          Key Technical Decisions
        </h2>

        <div
          class="features-grid"
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem;"
        >
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.03); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.08);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              Worker Pools for Exports
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.6;">
              Large dataset operations were blocking the event loop. Worker Pools
              moved heavy processing to parallel threads, keeping the API responsive
              while exports ran in the background. 45min became 12min.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.03); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.08);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              Profiler-Driven Optimization
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.6;">
              Instead of guessing at bottlenecks, I used the Node.js profiler to
              identify exactly where time was spent in the column filtering pipeline —
              then optimized the specific MongoDB aggregations that mattered.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.03); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.08);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              Dynamic Column Generation
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.6;">
              Energy projects have variable properties. The filtering system generates
              columns dynamically based on project characteristics — flexible enough
              for any project shape, fast enough for daily use.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            style="padding: 2rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.03); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.08);"
          >
            <h3
              style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--primary);"
            >
              TDD from Day One
            </h3>
            <p style="color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.6;">
              On a migration project, you're replacing a system people depend on.
              I introduced test-driven development for every feature — not because
              it was required, but because the risk of shipping broken replacements
              was too high.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- BUSINESS IMPACT -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          Business Impact
        </h2>

        <div
          class="metrics-grid"
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem; margin: 2.5rem 0;"
        >
          <div
            style="text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.05); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.1);"
          >
            <div
              style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"
            >
              65%
            </div>
            <div style="color: var(--gray); font-weight: 500;">
              Faster API Responses
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            style="text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.05); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.1);"
          >
            <div
              style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"
            >
              73%
            </div>
            <div style="color: var(--gray); font-weight: 500;">
              Faster Exports (45min → 12min)
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            style="text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(99,102,241,0.05); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.1);"
          >
            <div
              style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"
            >
              15K+
            </div>
            <div style="color: var(--gray); font-weight: 500;">
              Daily Queries Handled
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p
          style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray); margin-top: 1.5rem;"
        >
          The 65% API improvement meant energy traders could query market data and get
          answers fast enough to act on them. The export time reduction meant analysts
          stopped scheduling exports overnight — they could run them during the workday
          and iterate. The new architecture gave a 4-person team the ability to ship
          features that the old monolith made impossible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- WHAT I LEARNED -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          What I Took Away
        </h2>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"
        >
          This project taught me the value of <strong>consistency in delivery</strong>.
          On a small team replacing a production system, there's no room for erratic output.
          Every week needed to move the migration forward predictably. I learned to scope
          work tightly, ship reliably, and communicate progress clearly.
        </p>
        <p
          style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--gray);"
        >
          Technically, it deepened my conviction that performance optimization starts with
          measurement. The profiler-first approach — finding the real bottleneck before
          writing a single optimization — saved weeks of wasted effort and became a
          permanent part of how I work.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- TECH STACK -->
      <section
        class="content-section"
        style="background: var(--gradient-card); border-radius: 20px; padding: 3rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);"
      >
        <h2
          style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--dark);"
        >
          Technology Stack
        </h2>
        <div
          style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;"
        >
          {
            [
              { name: "NestJS", tech: "NestJS" },
              { name: "MongoDB", tech: "MongoDB" },
              { name: "TypeScript", tech: "TypeScript" },
              { name: "Docker", tech: "Docker" },
              { name: "Node.js", tech: "Node.js" },
              { name: "Worker Threads", tech: "Microservices" },
            ].map((item) => (
              <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1rem; background: var(--dark); color: white; border-radius: 16px; font-weight: 600; text-align: center; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); transition: all 0.3s ease; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; min-height: 100px; justify-content: center;">
                <TechIcon technology={item.tech} size={32} />
                <span style="font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.2;">
                  {item.name}
                </span>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  .project-hero h1 {
    color: white;
  }

  .content-section {
    animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease forwards;
  }

  @keyframes fadeInUp {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(30px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  .features-grid > div:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"]:hover {
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .project-hero {
      padding: 48px 0 32px;
    }

    .project-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.25rem;
    }

    .project-hero p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .content-section {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .metrics-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .features-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr))"] {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(110px, 1fr)) !important;
      gap: 1rem !important;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"] {
      min-height: 80px !important;
      padding: 1rem 0.75rem !important;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"] span:first-child {
      font-size: 1.5rem !important;
    }

    .content-section div[style*="min-height: 100px"] span:last-child {
      font-size: 0.8rem !important;
    }
  }
</style>
